# AutoGen: A Framework for Multi-Agent LLM Applications

**Repository**: [microsoft/autogen](https://github.com/microsoft/autogen)
**Paper**: [AutoGen: Enabling Next-Generation LLM Applications via Multi-Agent Conversation](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2308.08155.pdf)

## Technical Summary
AutoGen introduces a robust framework for developing multi-agent LLM applications through conversational interactions. The framework supports:
- Dynamic agent creation and customization
- Flexible conversation patterns beyond simple back-and-forth exchanges
- Built-in code execution environment
- Seamless integration of human inputs alongside AI agents

## Implementation Example
```python
from autogen import AssistantAgent, UserProxyAgent

# Initialize agents
assistant = AssistantAgent(
    name="coding_assistant",
    llm_config={"config_list": config_list}
)

user_proxy = UserProxyAgent(
    name="user_proxy",
    code_execution_config={"work_dir": "coding"}
)

# Start multi-agent conversation
user_proxy.initiate_chat(
    assistant,
    message="Let's solve this coding problem"
)
